&lt;div style="line-height: 1.6;"&gt;
Large Language Models demonstrate lower safety thresholds when used with low-resource languages like Singlish, Malay, and Tamil, leading to increased generation of toxic and biased content. This vulnerability is exacerbated by few-shot prompting techniques that bypass safety measures, particularly affecting conversational, question-answering, and content creation tasks.
